==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Doncella
<hw>Don*cel"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp., lit., a
maid. Cf. <er>Damsel</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A handsome
fish of Florida and the West Indies (<spn>Platyglossus radiatus</spn>).
The name is applied also to the ladyfish (<spn>Harpe rufa</spn>) of the
same region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

